SIMPLE: towering
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Towering
<hw>Tow"er*ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Very
high; elevated; rising aloft; <as>as, a <ex>towering</ex>
height</as>.</def> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, extreme; violent; surpassing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A man agitated by a <qex>towering</qex> passion.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Towery</ent>⟦br⟧
